UP|52|NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Another interesting hand and honest, these are random, not prearranged. It turns out the winning bid by West is double of 3D, but that is impossible to find which is another argument for preempting, because, even when double works out, it is difficult for the opponents to find the proper contract. West has a clear 3H bid with his hand. I think Ally should bid 3N with her hand and hope that they can scramble and take 9 tricks. |
PG| ***** 78 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If partner then pulls to 4H, she can correct to 4S. Her diamonds are probably not worth much in spades, but they have some value in NT. On the other hand, I don't think they do much better in 3N as it turns out because transportation between the hands is difficult. Now, the most important point I want to make is on opening leads which is the first topic of my upcoming course on defense. Next, is a preview of the first lesson. |
PG| ***** 79 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Here are some rules that I believe in. The most important is "you never lose the post mortem by leading partner's suit" I just about always lead partner's suit. On occasion it is wrong, but it is usually right or makes no difference. And partner knows when I don't lead his suit, I probably have a void, or a singleton in the suit that I did lead. So, I strongly recommend you always lead partner's suit if you can. |
PG| ***** 80 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Obviously Elizabeth could not in this case. However, she did violate another rule of mine. It is that it is rarely right to lead the opponent's suit (not counting trumps). So, a heart lead should be her last choice.  All she is doing is setting up the opponents suit. On this auction, Ally is likely to be shorter in hearts than spades. Therefore, I would have led a trump with Elizabeth's hand. A club would be okay. But a heart is not okay since West bid hearts.|
PG| ***** 81 ***** |


NT|^B@2
ELIZA42: I knew camilleln didn't have many spades therefore has fewer hearts.|
PG| ***** 82 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, lead a trump since you have heart tricks and use your A and K to capture honors from West. Often when declarer is two suited, a trump lead is right.|
PG| ***** 83 ***** |


